Unknown Gunmen have abducted two family members at Abuja Quarters in Mallammadori Local Government Area of Jigawa State. A resident who spoke to DAILY POST said the gunmen numbering about ten invaded Mallammadori town at midnight on Monday abducted the victims. He said the Gunmen shot sporadically, invaded the residence of one Abdullahi Blacki, a Bureau-de-change operator who resides in Lagos and abducted two of his children. He identified the victims as Najib Abdullahi and â€˜Yanmata Abdullahi, who are both teenagers at Junior secondary schools. Police spokesperson in Jigawa, Aminuddeen Zubair, confirmed the incident to DAILY POST. He said that police received the report and will get back to reporters with details.